column5: Betty and I got down to wait for the first leg of the flame.It was AWESOME.  Vids not the best,but something to share with the young,ns later in life.  I will be able to say,,I WAS THERE WHEN.LOL      GO CANADA GO
I guess all those plain clothed cops didn't attack anyone this time
one day to get to Barry from Port Elgin....least you guys had better weather  your right .."that was kewl"
After rereading,,,,,,,That statement,it means Im getting old,,,,,,,older.   No,,, wiser,thats it,wiser in my younger years.

I had the honor to carry the torch when it was in Barrie in 1988. Now almost 22 years later it was back and I shared it with my soon to be 1 year old son. I wonder what will happen in the next 22 years?        We were right by the DQ on Bradford St.
So do they run the torch 24x7 or only during the day?  I missed it in Barrie today, I wanna catch it somewhere else...  Even in the middle of nowhere is good enough for me.
Leaving Barrie Wednesday 8am. Here's the map:  http://www.vancouver2010.com/more-2010-inf...nteractive-map/
i'd watch it in the sault, but i think i'll be fishin!
...."middle of nowhwere?"  It's here in elliot lake in a few...the ice is hard and the beers are cold!
That's a great video, thanks for sharing.  Wife and I planned to go originally, but we felt it was just too cold out to take our 4 month old.
They are going to float it down the Notty, get the pin ready.
So i hope that the world Olympic committee is paying for all those cop cars and the police officer that are on overtime. Waste of tax payers money.
